      • hasMessageBodyInputPort

        public static boolean hasMessageBodyInputPort(RESTActivity.HTTP_METHOD httpMethod)
        Return value of this method has a number of implications - various input ports and configuration options for this activity are applied based on the selected HTTP method.
        Parameters:
        httpMethod - HTTP method to make the decision for.
        Returns:
        True if this instance of the REST activity uses HTTP POST / PUT methods; false otherwise.

      • executeAsynch

        public void executeAsynch(Map<String,T2Reference> inputs,
                          AsynchronousActivityCallback callback)
        This method executes pre-configured instance of REST activity. It resolves inputs of the activity and registers its outputs; the real invocation of the HTTP request is performed by HTTPRequestHandler#initiateHTTPRequest(String, RESTActivityConfigurationBean, String) .
        Specified by:
        executeAsynch in interface AsynchronousActivity<com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode>
